<div class="container-fluid" align="center">
	
	<h2>To add a video, first, select a team. If your team isn't there, go to the "Add Team" tab.</h2>
	<select name="teamSelect" ng-model="team" ng-change="getAllGames()">
		<% @teams.each do |team| %>
		<option value="<%= team['objectId']%>"><%=team['team_name']%></option>
		<%end%>
	</select>
	
	<h2>Add an opponent. If your opponent isn't there, go to the "Add Team" tab.</h2>
	<select name="opponentSelect" ng-model="addTeamOpponent">
		<% @teams.each do |team| %>
		<option value="<%= team['objectId']%>"><%=team['team_name']%></option>
		<%end%>
	</select>

	<h2>Next, pick a year the video happened</h2>
	<p>Based on the fall year. So a video that took place in spring 2015 should be listed as fall year 2014</p>
	<p>Hint: We are currently in fall year 2019</p>
	<select ng-model="fallYear">
		<option value="2012">2012</option>
		<option value="2013">2013</option>
		<option value="2014">2014</option>
		<option value="2015">2015</option>
		<option value="2016">2016</option>
		<option value="2017">2017</option>
		<option value="2018">2018</option>
		<option value="2019">2019</option>
		<option selected value="2020">2020</option>
		<option value="2021">2021</option>
	</select>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid">

<div class="container-fluid" align="center">
	<h2>Then, go to the video you wish to add on youtube. There, take the video id, as shown, and paste it in to the box</h2>
		<img src="/images/youtube_link_helper.jpg"/>
		<br>
		<br>
		<form>
			<input ng-model="vidPreview" type="text"><br>
		</form>
	</div>

	<div class="container-fluid" align="center">
		<h2>Add a description</h2>
		<p>Ex: WCVII vs. NYDC</p>
		<p>WC7 NYDC</p>
		<p>Or something similarly succient</p>
		<input type="text" ng-model="vidDesc"/>
	</div>


	<div class="container-fluid" align="center">
		<h2> Is this your desired video?</h2>
		<div>
			<youtube-video video-id="vidPreview" player="videoPreviewer" class="embed-responsive-item" player-width="'65%'"></youtube-video>
			<h2> Then hit the "Add" button, and you're good to go </h2>
		<button class="btn btn-lg" ng-click="addVideo()">Add</button>
		<br>
		<br>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="helpText" class="white_content">
	<a href = "javascript:void(0)" onclick = "document.getElementById('helpText').style.display='none';document.getElementById('fade').style.display='none'">Close<br></a>
	
	<h4>Follow the instructions on screen.</h4>

	<a href = "javascript:void(0)" onclick = "document.getElementById('helpText').style.display='none';document.getElementById('fade').style.display='none'">Close<br></a>
</div>
<div id="fade" class="black_overlay"></div>